Durban - Hundreds of community members in Mbuthumeni village outside Harding, southern KwaZulu-Natal, have been digging day and night believing that they will strike it rich with the discovery of “gold” in the area.
This comes after road construction workers, who had been digging in the area, found glittery rocks almost two weeks ago.



People are travelling from as far as Durban, Pietermaritzburg, the Eastern Cape and Johannesburg to witness the spectacle, but mainly to try to find gold for themselves.

While many hope and believe it’s gold, others just think it’s “fool’s gold”.

The area falls under traditional leadership of iNkosi Mthetho Machi and by extension also belongs to the Ingonyama Trust.

When The Mercury visited yesterday, the site was a hive of activity with more than 2000 people digging, while youngsters carrying digging tools were running out with bags full of “gold ”.















